p: \b\pn. You need to see this. It's important.
\bWhile you were in the pyramid... something happened here.
\bI know, right? Understatement of the century.
\bOne of our field agents here reported a battle between two powerful Pokemon.
\bOnly a legendary Pokemon could cause this much destruction so quickly.
\b...but there aren't very many Ground or Rock-type legendaries.
\bRegirock doesn't have any enemies as far as we know, and I feel like we'd know if Kyogre and Groudon were here.
\bIt MUST be a Delta. It MUST be.
\bThey said I was crazy. They said a Delta Species legendary was a fantasy. An impossible dream.
\bBut I'll find one. I'll show them. I'll show them ALL!
\b...anyways, please keep me updated.\nLet me know if you see these mysterious Pokemon or find evidence of fighting.
\bI'll call you. I'm going to head up to Settlement Juliet.
\bYou might want to head north, too, when you're done here.
\bThere's a lake, a mountain, and more that way.
There seems to be some kind of notch on the rock.
Perhaps a Pokemon could tunnel their way through with a move?
Battle: \bIt's a bit hard to navigate the desert... but some of the incredible Pokemon here make it completely worthwhile!

Battle: \bClearly, normal people couldn't have built that pyramid! There's no way that ancient people were as smart as we are. It must have been aliens.
EndSpeech: What do you mean... conspiracy?

Battle: \bThat looks a lot like an arrow.

Battle: \rI wonder what kind of ancient technology could be found within that pyramid. Maybe we can repurpose it for our own uses!
EndSpeech: Oh, I can't wait to find out! Genies, magic carpets, maybe?
